DSA-CH23 – Simplified Social Network (A5: Friend Search / Autocomplete)

Project Overview

This project implements a simplified social network feature that allows users to search for friends quickly using an autocomplete system. The system suggests friend names as the user types a prefix.

The implementation uses the Trie (Prefix Tree) data structure to provide efficient and scalable prefix-based searching.

This project demonstrates the use of key Data Structures and Algorithms concepts such as searching, prefix indexing, and complexity analysis.

---

Features

- Add friend names
- Fast prefix-based friend search
- Autocomplete suggestions
- Case-insensitive searching
- Efficient scalable search using Trie structure

